1
00:01:26,688 --> 00:01:30,599
<i>[Begin Again]</i>

2
00:01:30,599 --> 00:01:33,128
Isn't it amazing?

3
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:36,439
Senna, right?

4
00:01:37,079 --> 00:01:38,439
He

5
00:01:38,439 --> 00:01:41,760
is the true racing god in my heart.

6
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:42,959
In the first Macau F3 race,

7
00:01:42,959 --> 00:01:45,640
he was the champion.

8
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:47,400
Not long after that race,

9
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:49,599
he officially entered Formula 1.

10
00:01:49,599 --> 00:01:50,640
I remember there was one race

11
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,439
that was particularly exciting.

12
00:01:52,439 --> 00:01:54,000
It was the Monaco race.

13
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,519
Not long into the race,

14
00:01:55,519 --> 00:01:56,599
it started to rain.

15
00:01:56,599 --> 00:01:57,920
All the drivers

16
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,319
slowed down.

17
00:01:59,319 --> 00:02:00,680
He was the only one

18
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:03,120
who did not slow down but sped up instead,

19
00:02:06,719 --> 00:02:09,560
as if he wanted to smash the accelerator.

20
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,000
He went from the 16th place,

21
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:13,759
all the way to the second place.

22
00:02:13,759 --> 00:02:15,400
The then-reigning champion, I guess,

23
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:16,639
felt threatened,

24
00:02:16,639 --> 00:02:18,120
so he used the excuse of safety

25
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:20,120
and stopped the race.

26
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,120
Otherwise, I believe

27
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,280
he would have been the champion that day.

28
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:24,439
That trophy would have been his.

29
00:02:24,439 --> 00:02:27,112
Such a pity.

30
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,879
Would you do the same?

31
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:35,360
Not caring about safety during the race

32
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:37,704
and only wanting to win?

33
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:43,039
How should I put it?

34
00:02:43,039 --> 00:02:45,240
I think it's instinct.

35
00:02:45,879 --> 00:02:48,264
Instinct?

36
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:50,520
What happened later?

37
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,439
A case of a bright flame burning quickly.

38
00:02:52,439 --> 00:02:54,000
A car accident

39
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,719
took his life.

40
00:02:56,719 --> 00:02:57,919
On the day of his funeral,

41
00:02:57,919 --> 00:02:59,120
millions of Brazilians

42
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:01,000
took to the streets for his funeral procession.

43
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,719
I still distinctly remember
the words of an old man.

44
00:03:03,719 --> 00:03:06,960
Brazilians need

45
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:10,840
food and joy,

46
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:13,280
but today,

47
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:15,719
their joy is gone.

48
00:03:17,759 --> 00:03:20,000
Actually, I really understand Senna.

49
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,599
I understand his desire to win every time.

50
00:03:22,599 --> 00:03:24,800
It wasn't just for his own glory.

51
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:26,800
It was more

52
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:29,719
for his country behind him.

53
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:32,840
So, every victory

54
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:35,159
gave the Brazilians

55
00:03:35,159 --> 00:03:37,319
who were in the dark

56
00:03:37,319 --> 00:03:39,919
hope for the future.

57
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:44,280
He is truly great.

58
00:03:54,784 --> 00:04:00,159
<i>[Episode 10]</i>

59
00:04:00,159 --> 00:04:02,560
On the list

60
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,960
of past champions back there,

61
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:06,439
there were only two Chinese names.

62
00:04:07,479 --> 00:04:09,576
Yes.

63
00:04:11,039 --> 00:04:13,280
The home field of racing is in Europe.

64
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:16,759
So, in the past, Chinese drivers

65
00:04:16,759 --> 00:04:19,560
were not allowed to participate.

66
00:04:21,279 --> 00:04:22,720
I get it.

67
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:25,360
If I were you, I would also
find it hard to accept.

68
00:04:27,319 --> 00:04:28,800
Haven't I told you before?

69
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,279
When I was racing abroad,

70
00:04:30,279 --> 00:04:32,360
those foreign drivers

71
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:34,120
didn't really know me.

72
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:36,319
Then they mocked and ridiculed me,

73
00:04:36,319 --> 00:04:38,240
saying 'Do Chinese drivers

74
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:40,240
really know how to race?'

75
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:42,279
Because of this comment,

76
00:04:42,279 --> 00:04:43,800
I swore to myself

77
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:46,800
that I would beat every single one of them.

78
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:48,079
So on the race track,

79
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:50,160
I show no mercy.

80
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:52,199
I just want to let them know

81
00:04:52,199 --> 00:04:53,439
that in Chinese motorsports,

82
00:04:53,439 --> 00:04:55,079
we started late,

83
00:04:55,079 --> 00:04:57,560
but we can drive fast.

84
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,439
What's the matter?

85
00:05:06,439 --> 00:05:07,639
The way you spoke just now.

86
00:05:07,639 --> 00:05:09,120
You were so arrogant.

87
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:10,319
Was I?

88
00:05:10,319 --> 00:05:12,399
But it's cute.

89
00:05:13,319 --> 00:05:14,319
Only cute?

90
00:05:14,319 --> 00:05:17,096
Handsome.

91
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,519
Next time we come here,

92
00:05:20,519 --> 00:05:22,000
the name Han Junhao

93
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:25,040
will appear on that list.

94
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:27,560
Do you really have

95
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:28,959
so much confidence in me?

96
00:05:28,959 --> 00:05:31,920
Yes, I told you I have
a very accurate sixth sense.

97
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:42,319
Why do the clothes here seem a bit old?

98
00:05:42,319 --> 00:05:43,720
This is a vintage store.

99
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:45,759
They sell things that are no longer

100
00:05:45,759 --> 00:05:48,399
produced in the market.

101
00:05:50,639 --> 00:05:52,720
What is this?

102
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:55,319
A TV set.

103
00:05:55,319 --> 00:05:57,920
Is this what you watched as a child?

104
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:02,079
This TV set

105
00:06:02,079 --> 00:06:05,360
is older than you and me combined.

106
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:08,439
It's so small I thought it was a bread maker.

107
00:06:10,639 --> 00:06:12,480
There's a hairstyle

108
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,480
that I think suits you well.

109
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:16,839
Take a look.

110
00:06:16,839 --> 00:06:18,759
And glasses too.

111
00:06:18,759 --> 00:06:20,872
Come on.

112
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:30,024
Three.

113
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:38,879
This one looks pretty good.

114
00:06:38,879 --> 00:06:40,319
A bald head, huh?

115
00:06:40,319 --> 00:06:43,399
Oh my God.

116
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:50,856
Do you like it?

117
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:58,720
- Is it okay?
- So-so.

118
00:06:58,720 --> 00:07:00,439
Why such a low neckline?

119
00:07:00,439 --> 00:07:02,600
Isn't it too low?

120
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:07,800
- Come on, give a twirl.
- Why?

121
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:09,920
This suits you.

122
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,800
Having known you for so long,

123
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:38,480
this is your best look.

124
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,079
Sorry, sorry, ma'am.

125
00:07:42,079 --> 00:07:43,560
We've been trying for so long.

126
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:45,800
We'll take these two sets.

127
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:48,160
It's all right, watching you
change clothes is fun.

128
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:51,319
You're so stylish, why don't I
take a photo for you?

129
00:07:51,319 --> 00:07:52,439
Sure.

130
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:54,839
Come on, look at the camera.

131
00:07:54,839 --> 00:07:56,879
Come on, look over here.

132
00:07:56,879 --> 00:07:59,560
Cheese.

133
00:08:13,639 --> 00:08:14,759
Qiang.

134
00:08:14,759 --> 00:08:16,959
Today I asked Junhao to come back

135
00:08:16,959 --> 00:08:19,319
and have a good chat with you.

136
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:24,319
Hao, have a good chat with your dad.

137
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:34,920
Dad, have some tea.

138
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,480
Actually, I came today

139
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:52,679
to say sorry.

140
00:08:52,679 --> 00:08:54,600
I should have told you earlier

141
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,440
about Jiajia and me.

142
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:59,080
Perhaps I've been used to solving
problems by myself all my life,

143
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:03,360
so I neglected your feelings.

144
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:05,279
I'm sorry.

145
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:08,159
After I went back yesterday,
Jiajia talked a lot to me

146
00:09:08,159 --> 00:09:10,679
and she made me understand

147
00:09:10,679 --> 00:09:11,720
the big reaction everyone had

148
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:14,879
was all because you cared about me.

149
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,559
You see,

150
00:09:20,559 --> 00:09:23,159
Jiajia is so well-behaved, sensible,

151
00:09:23,159 --> 00:09:24,159
and mature.

152
00:09:24,159 --> 00:09:27,480
Jiajia sees things more clearly than you.

153
00:09:30,159 --> 00:09:33,480
Speak frankly to your dad.

154
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,639
Jiajia is a

155
00:09:40,639 --> 00:09:43,159
kind and mature girl.

156
00:09:43,159 --> 00:09:44,679
Although she is young,

157
00:09:44,679 --> 00:09:48,360
she is more mature in many aspects than I am.

158
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:51,679
I know Jiajia is a good girl,

159
00:09:51,679 --> 00:09:55,039
but you have only known
each other for half a year.

160
00:09:55,039 --> 00:09:57,639
Why get married so quickly?

161
00:09:57,639 --> 00:10:00,799
Dad, I think you should understand

162
00:10:00,799 --> 00:10:03,679
that when you truly meet

163
00:10:03,679 --> 00:10:04,679
the one,

164
00:10:04,679 --> 00:10:07,559
you won't want any delay.

165
00:10:07,559 --> 00:10:09,600
I just want to marry her and
bring her home as soon as possible

166
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:12,960
to have a family of my own.

167
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:17,200
I'm not against your marriage.

168
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:20,159
Even if you really want to get married,

169
00:10:20,159 --> 00:10:21,159
you need time

170
00:10:21,159 --> 00:10:23,360
to prepare for your wedding.

171
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:25,320
You need to decide whom to invite.

172
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:28,559
Some things can't be rushed.

173
00:10:28,559 --> 00:10:29,559
I know, Dad.

174
00:10:29,559 --> 00:10:30,600
That's why actually,

175
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,919
we have already been preparing
for quite some time.

176
00:10:32,919 --> 00:10:34,879
It's just during the preparation process,

177
00:10:34,879 --> 00:10:38,240
I didn't think it was necessary to trouble you.

178
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,559
Besides, Jiajia and I

179
00:10:39,559 --> 00:10:41,799
don't care much for ceremonies.

180
00:10:41,799 --> 00:10:44,679
We just want to use this wedding to tell people

181
00:10:44,679 --> 00:10:47,120
who care about me

182
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:49,360
that we want to be together

183
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:50,480
for a lifetime.

184
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:52,440
That's it.

185
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:54,799
But marriage

186
00:10:54,799 --> 00:10:57,879
is not just about two people.

187
00:10:57,879 --> 00:11:00,559
It involves two families.

188
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:03,679
You are my son.

189
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:07,480
Can I do nothing when you get married?

190
00:11:08,039 --> 00:11:10,240
Can I attend my son's wedding

191
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:13,799
like attending a friend's wedding?

192
00:11:13,799 --> 00:11:16,200
How will the parents of the bride

193
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,639
think of us?

194
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,600
Honestly, Dad,

195
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,120
even if I had told you in advance,

196
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:25,720
hoping for your involvement,

197
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:28,360
would you have had the time for me?

198
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,440
You are at Zhen Qiang day and night.

199
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,600
I've known this for a long time.

200
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:34,639
Why bring up Zhen Qiang?

201
00:11:34,639 --> 00:11:36,200
What does Zhen Qiang have to do with this?

202
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:38,200
But that's the reality.

203
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,399
All the time in your life

204
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:41,039
has been spent on Zhen Qiang.

205
00:11:41,039 --> 00:11:42,039
Have you ever thought

206
00:11:42,039 --> 00:11:44,639
that you could take it easier at your age?

207
00:11:44,639 --> 00:11:46,200
To not work so hard?

208
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,240
I've told you many times.

209
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,679
I can help you sell it.

210
00:11:48,679 --> 00:11:50,200
Enough.

211
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,440
You keep talking

212
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:52,879
about selling Zhen Qiang.

213
00:11:52,879 --> 00:11:54,159
I didn't say we have to sell it.

214
00:11:54,159 --> 00:11:55,440
Stop it.

215
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,919
If you have time,

216
00:11:56,919 --> 00:11:58,639
focus on your wedding.

217
00:11:58,639 --> 00:12:00,240
Do it however you want to.

218
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:02,759
I won't interfere with it anymore.

219
00:12:02,759 --> 00:12:04,200
What are you doing?

220
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:06,440
I don't want to talk anymore.

221
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:10,279
Hao, I asked you to come back

222
00:12:10,279 --> 00:12:12,000
and clear things up with your dad.

223
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,559
Why did it end on bad terms again?

224
00:12:13,559 --> 00:12:15,399
I tried my best.

225
00:12:15,399 --> 00:12:18,360
I really can't communicate with him.

226
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:21,000
Sorry, Mom.

227
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:24,600
Jiajia's parents will be here soon.

228
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,039
I don't even know.

229
00:12:26,039 --> 00:12:28,279
We'll see.

230
00:12:28,279 --> 00:12:31,000
Rest assured.

231
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,000
Thank you, Mom.

232
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:41,559
Fighting again?

233
00:12:41,559 --> 00:12:43,559
Is it about the wedding again?

234
00:12:43,559 --> 00:12:45,159
I don't understand. What's there

235
00:12:45,159 --> 00:12:47,519
to fight about?

236
00:12:47,519 --> 00:12:48,759
Don't bother with them anymore.

237
00:12:48,759 --> 00:12:53,399
They are adults, let them cool down.

238
00:12:53,399 --> 00:12:54,879
You've tried.

239
00:12:54,879 --> 00:12:57,384
Bye.

240
00:12:59,879 --> 00:13:01,600
Is there a problem at home?

241
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:04,000
My dad and brother are fighting again.

242
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,440
Do you want to rush home and check on it?

243
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:07,679
I don't want to go back.

244
00:13:07,679 --> 00:13:10,200
Anyway, whatever I say, they won't listen.

245
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:12,559
Besides, they are all adults.
Let them solve it themselves.

246
00:13:12,559 --> 00:13:13,559
In that case,

247
00:13:13,559 --> 00:13:15,679
let's find a place

248
00:13:15,679 --> 00:13:18,919
to take a walk and get some air, okay?

249
00:13:18,919 --> 00:13:21,000
Aren't you hungry?

250
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,159
We'll eat after the walk.

251
00:13:23,159 --> 00:13:25,512
Okay.

252
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,639
This is the first time

253
00:13:52,639 --> 00:13:55,120
I've seen you walk so fast.

254
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:01,919
You're worried about Mr. Xu, right?

255
00:14:12,759 --> 00:14:15,039
Actually, I've always known

256
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:17,600
that I am the best person

257
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:20,679
to take over the restaurant at home.

258
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:24,440
My brother has his own things he wants to do.

259
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:26,919
And Bao is still young.

260
00:14:26,919 --> 00:14:29,159
But when she grows up,

261
00:14:29,159 --> 00:14:32,159
she'll certainly have her own pursuits.

262
00:14:33,559 --> 00:14:34,960
What about you?

263
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:38,039
Don't you have a life you want to pursue?

264
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:41,720
I'm the kind of person

265
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:45,000
who doesn't have many desires.

266
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:47,279
I just want to live in the present

267
00:14:47,279 --> 00:14:49,039
and to do well in the things at hand.

268
00:14:49,039 --> 00:14:51,480
That's enough for me.

269
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:54,088
It's just…

270
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:58,720
It's just that you're afraid of messing up.

271
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:00,399
You fear wasting the many
years of effort put in by Mr. Xu

272
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:03,039
will be ruined in your hands.

273
00:15:06,799 --> 00:15:08,759
You probably haven't seen

274
00:15:08,759 --> 00:15:11,279
the other side of Zhen Qiang.

275
00:15:13,879 --> 00:15:15,240
- Hello!
- Table for three.

276
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:16,320
Our shop

277
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:18,840
starts business at 5 PM.

278
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:20,399
There are many customers.

279
00:15:20,399 --> 00:15:21,960
The staff is busy

280
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:24,120
until early morning.

281
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,919
After Mr. Qiang finishes the day's accounts,

282
00:15:38,919 --> 00:15:41,000
he has to go to the market to buy groceries.

283
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,240
This is how we ensure

